Subject: Allotment (26th Oct - 11am)

Body:
Hi all,

In continuation to the discussion had on 22nd Oct (Saturday) on subject implementation. Phase-wise implementation will happen to ensure smooth rollout.

Phase I - Week 43  (24th Oct  29th Oct)
1) Since there are some showstoppers on confirm activity task in PTS Kumar Sir, will modify PTS to capture both WIP hours and actual manual hours by Friday (28th
October). Currently the actual hours should be 8 hours to close the confirm activity task, if the actual hour update is deactivated it will not be possible to close the task
2) Trial run will happen this week to capture the possible issues faced
3) All tickets thru any format (Mail, chat, calls) will be recorded in PTS and monitored by the heads
4)Team heads will follow-up with the team members on usage of WIP
5) Weekly allotment report will be send on daily basis
Phase II  Week 44 (31st Oct  5th Nov)
1) Dual run  Both WIP hours and manual actual hours will be captured in PTS
2) Leads will evaluate the difference in gap between the actual hours and the manual hours on daily basis
3) Regular Feebdack and coaching will be given to the Team members 
Phase III  Week 45 (7th Nov  12th Nov)
1) Based on the outcome of Phase II, the manual hours update in PTS will be disabled 
2) Kumar, will do the necessary changes in PTS to disable the manual hours updated 
3)  Go Live will be on Week 45 (10 th Nov)
Please approach self if need any clarifications

Regards

Stephen

-----

Third Floor,New No 42 / Old No-4,
Second Line Beach,Parrys,
Chennai - 600 001.(India)

Body:
Good Morning all
RIC  Subhranshu , please issue the tickets 

Meeting with in regards to

Centralized payment process in EBMSAuto -seamless flow in Books of Accounts from Liner/FFD/ Flexi module

Concall was held amongst Rajna Mam, Rajeev, Subhranshu & Mujib (EBMS), in relation above processes to be set in EBMS 

Following is concluded as below

1.Auto seamless flow from ops (Liner : Vasco & GMLLC/FFD/Flexi module) to FAS

Invoice

Here , primary check will be Invoice print , when invoice print is triggered of the FINAL INVOICE , the auto posting in accounts will be effected.The posting will be real time and automated totally only for transactions which are clear viz : Customer & charges are mapped with FAS.If the invoice is created for which customer or charges is not mapped, alert will be sent to designated users , but system will also to generate invoice.

This will collate in the existing posting module. Once the F&A HO team does the necessary mapping /approval of customer & Charge code into
FAS , the invoice will be appear for posting and the accounts user will have this posted using the Invoice/credit note/receipt posting module to FAS

Credit Notes
 Credit notes will be automatically posted to FAS from Accounts . 
 There should be approver concept . When a user issue credit notes , it should be approved by Approver(HOD/BM/anointed user) and then
only the credit note should be allowed to be generated /taken 
print and posted to FAS
. The Credit note Report in operation should shows /capture all the log from request of credit note to approval to issuance /posting.

Receipts : 
 Receipts will be auto posted from all these ops module to Accounts.
 Ebms to give master table where in Goodrich HO defines location wise/module wise cash and bank ledgers
 By default this bank details will be fetched at time of receipt generation. 

For New forwarding module , this feature is already be asked for in GAP itself , it is part of package , NO ENHANCEMENT. 

Tickets for auto posting needs to raised by ERP team one each for each module.

2. Centralized Bank Payment Process

All payments /designated payments will be centralized from HO.

The purchase bills will be booked at branches as the existing practice.For bills will be settled from HO , Branch user will selecting the same and scheduling it .The HO Disbursement Bank account will be selected at HO .Table/interface/Master for the same to be with Goodrich. These bills can be seen by the anointed HO users for payments ( Table /master/interface providing rights should be with Goodrich)HO user selects these invoices of various branches (but one vendor) and makes the payment . Proper & intelligent payment interface should be provided
by EBMS teamThere will one Branch wise Control account for accounting purposeIn case of branch control account entries for centralised payment, same has to be auto created and posted .HO team will only select the invoices popping
up for payment.Entry will be :-

IN HO BOOKS (MANUAL PAYMENT ENTRY THROUGH THE INTERFACE PROVIDED )
Dr Branch control Account
Cr Bank

IN BRANCH BOOKS (AUTOMATED & LINKED TO HO PAYMENT ENTRY)
 Dr Vendor /Customer 
 Cr Branch Control Account

Ticket for Centralized bank process to provided by ERP Team

Tentative completion date to satisfaction of the Goodrich user will be on or before 15th of August 2019
